{
  "stem": "21786.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With the onset of the anti-Jewish laws and bylaws, the neighbors and the population around us simply started to be afraid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They knew perfectly well that they are not supposed to have any contact with Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Any kind of help, any kind of association would mean arrest and further, probably transportation to a camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, one of the German-- one of the special orders was to put more Jews together somehow to concentrate them, so that some people were moved out of their homes and moved to another family's, to-- to another Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like, to our apartment came [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] another six persons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were three families.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Two of them we knew very well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then was one couple who were originally from Germany and one couple who was, I think, from Austria caught in the territory of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In others words, they didn't leave in time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, the same happened practically to every Jewish family, so that they have been condensed together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, this everybody in Prague was registered with the police, which still exists simply that your domicile is registered with the police.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In other words, if you are looking for somebody you can go just to the police registry, and you found out where the person lives.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "At that point it was extremely tight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had a-- a kind of a ID, passes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And on the ID pass of every Jew was written J as Jew, so that it was quite obvious if you would have to show a document so everybody would know.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can tell you only one family name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of them, it was a Reiter, R-E-I-T-E-R.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His first name was Karel Charles, K-A-R-E-L.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And her name was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Sonja, S-O-N-J-A.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
